The paper deals with algorithmic techniques for computing the Hamming distance between a pattern and a text, which is a fundamental problem in string algorithms. This problem is related to sparse recovery, which suggests that the paper may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also introduces a new construction of hash/projection functions, which may suggest that it belongs to cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Additionally, the paper discusses lower bounds for computing the Hamming distance, which may suggest that it belongs to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
